<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Yes. I've had my fishing skill cap at (level+1)*5, and I fish regulary. As I'm a mage, mostly I sell what I catch to the same vendor I buy my bait from, and am able to earn about one silver per fish gross.<br>
As far as using it as a trade skill. I've seen, and accidentally purchased, the tacklebox. (I then sold it back, thinking it was a toolbox varient after all, since I've, until now, seen NOTHING on fishing being a trade skill.) On one of the islands in the Ocean of Tears, I've bought one of three different offerings of hooks, (then was dissappointed when I couldn't use it to fish with directly, I sold them back in Felwithe.)<p>

Does anyone know some recipes yet? I keep my fishing skill maxed to my level and am ready to try one. After my next mailbag run to Freeport of course.<p>

Good luck,<p>

Sean<p>

